source: This module generates and exposes a GraphQL schema for Drupal 8 entities, and allows you to expose your own custom schema in a consistent way and with minimal effort.
A DOM element located at a specific path.
A unique machine-readable name for this server. It must only contain lowercase letters, numbers, and underscores.
Add debugMessage key containing the exception message to errors.
Allows users to create, edit and delete server configurations.

Allows users to execute persisted requests on the %name endpoint.
Allows users to use the voyager interface.
Allows users use the explorer interface.
Base module for integrating GraphQL with Drupal.
